user.biography: The GPU, our invention, is the engine of computer graphics and GPU deep learning has ignited modern AI — the next era of computing.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by NVIDIA on August 30, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and outdoors.

node.text:
With the rise of herbicide-resistant weeds, farms everywhere face rising costs and increased soil contamination. NVIDIA Inception partner Greeneye is using the Jetson edge #AI platform, TensorRT and GPU-accelerated technologies to help farmers reduce chemicals and costs.

Learn more in our Inception highlight and story.

Powered by the NVIDIA accelerated computing platform, the Polaris #supercomputer at the Argonne National Laboratory will supercharge scientific research and discovery with extreme scale, allowing users to enter the era of #exascale.

Introducing NVIDIA Enterprise-Ready Software for #AI. It’s powerful, flexible, and available today from NVIDIA-Certified partners.

Learn more in our Enterprise story and profile highlight.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by NVIDIA on August 19, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'ACCELERATION ENGINE CONNECTX-6DX DX NETWORKINTERFACE INTERFACE PROGRAMMABLE ARM CORES 대O ACCELERATION ENGINE PCIE GEN PEEN4.0 4.0 SWITCH DDR4 MEMORY INTERFACE'.

node.text:
The tech world this week gets its first look under the hood of our NVIDIA BlueField #DPU. It’s already being embraced by cloud services, supercomputers and many OEMs and software partners.

Learn more in our DPU highlight and story.

Autonomous trucking startup Embark is planning for universal autonomy of commercial semi-trucks, developing one #AI platform that fits all. The company announced that it will use NVIDIA DRIVE to develop its Embark Universal Interface (EUI), a manufacturer-agnostic platform that includes the compute and multimodal sensors necessary for autonomous trucks. This flexible approach, combined with the high performance of #NVIDIADRIVE, leads to an easily scalable solution for safer, more efficient delivery and logistics.

node.text: Our founder and CEO, Jensen Huang, has transformed how technology solves the world’s hardest challenges. The Semiconductor Industry Association (SIA) recognizes his contributions to the #semiconductor industry by awarding him the 2021 Robert N. Noyce Award—the industry's highest honor.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by NVIDIA on August 11, 2021. May be an image of text.

node.text:
With @NVIDIAOmniverse,  our team of artists, researchers and engineers were able to collaborate using different industry content-creation tools like Autodesk Maya or Substance Painter while in different places to create the NVIDIA #GTC21 keynote, filled with cutting-edge demos highlighting advancements in supercomputing, deep learning and graphics.

Learn more about what we revealed at #SIGGRAPH2021 in our SIGGRAPH highlight.

node.text:
Introducing the new low-profile #NVIDIARTX A2000 bringing real-time ray tracing, AI-accelerated compute, and high-performance #graphics to your desktop workstation.

Learn more from our RTX A2000 highlight and story.

The NVIDIA Inception program has hit a milestone, ramping 8.5K of #AI startups worldwide. The program supports and educates developers at every stage of their #startup journey. 

Learn more on the program in our Inception story and highlight.

node.text:
Discover what’s next in #graphics, AI, and the emergence of shared worlds during the NVIDIA special address on on August 10, 8:00 AM PDT, at #SIGGRAPH2021 with Richard Kerris, VP of Omniverse, and Sanja Fidler, Sr. Director AI Research.
